❤️ Happi ❤️
•
Diagnosed with Hep B & malaria, Happi spent two months in quarantine at the @orangutan_cop rescue centre undergoing intensive care to regain his health & strength 😢
•
Once well enough, he was moved to the baby socialisation area where he could make friends with other orphaned baby orangutans 🤗 Happi met Popi, and the two became best friends 👯‍♀️ Carers could see Happi growing in confidence with he’s new fiend by his side 😍
•
Forest school🌳 was very daunting for such a little guy 😬 and he would often cry out for his mother he was so nervous & scared 😟
•
Happi now LOVES jungle school ❤️🌳 and is rewarded by his carers with his favourite fruit - papaya 🍈- when he is very brave ☺️
•
At barely 2 years old, Happi has such a long way to go until he is able to be released into the protected forests.. could you support his journey?! 😄 Adopting Happi or one of his orphaned friends ensures he learns vital skills to be a wild orangutan 🐵 Click the link in our bio to adopt this cute little guy 👆🏻👆🏻#theorangutanproject

Meet Justin! All these adorable gargoyle heads are killing me! ♥️ Repost from @northcentralshelter |
Do you need some sunshine in your life? Jovial Justin is a bubbly character who constantly makes us smile with a slight cock of his head and twinkle in his eyes. He doesn't even know he's being cute!
At 2.5 years old, he is a bundle of puppy exuberance who would make an excellent jogging partner. 👣🐾 Justin loves playing fetch and has adored everyone he's met so far. He is treat-motivated and already knows sit, shake, and down! Come teach him new tricks!

Justin is an adorable, friendly, and playful 65 lbs., brindle, neutered male who has been at the shelter since Dec 26, 2017. Please come meet this lovable tail-wagger and give him a chance at a forever home today! And don’t forget to SHARE!
🌞⚾ JUSTIN #A1675613

I got nominated for the #10factsaboutmydog challenge by my German cousin @bringalittlejoy! So we’ll start with my first encounter with my mom.. 1️⃣ mom didn’t call the shelter for me but the dog she was looking at was already adopted so she settled for the best 😉 2️⃣ I have terrible coordination and often fall over myself and hit my head on things.. but I always come out fine 3️⃣ I was diagnosed with epilepsy after my adoption which was a very scary surprise 4️⃣ I make a lot of silly faces and do a lot of goofy things like laying on my back, paws in the air chewing on my toys 5️⃣ I can pretty much fall asleep anywhere.. including the middle of a heavily trafficked bridge in Yosemite 6️⃣ I have terrible separation anxiety that I have been working on lately 7️⃣ I have really cute freckles on my toes 😍 8️⃣ I am very submissive when it comes to playing with other dogs and I let them take my toys from me usually :/ 9️⃣ My absolute best friend is my mom.. and my puppy-sister Mia 🔟 My favorite things to chase are balls, ropes, and occasionally my own tail!
I tagged a few people that I thought would be good to do the challenge!
Thanks for all the facts, Brady❤️
What who is Mia?!? Also that was Roo’s name when I met her lol
@rooandrhaegar Mia is a yellow lab rescue we adopted when I was in elementary school! Are any of your dogs from ACT?

@bradytherescueshep yea Roo! We wanted our third from there but logistically wasn’t going to happen because he’s leaving so soon and we would have to drive there lol but in the future we plan on adopting from ACT even though it’s super difficult to get a dog back here 😂
@rooandrhaegar you’re still adopting more?! You’re gonna be a super dogmom lol How do you do it alone with 3?

@bradytherescueshep haha not anytime soon. But I sorta want a small fluff ball and eventually we want like 10 on some acreage. But I also want to be able to go on vacations with them and stuff so I can’t get toooo carried away for like 15 years 😂😂
@rooandrhaegar ugh that would be a dream! I hope it happens for you!
